Sentencas: Bi-layer La0.5Sr0.5CoO3-delta (LSCO) cathodes are processed by a hybrid method that combines a seed layer prepared by a pulsed laser deposition (PLD) technique and a conventional cathode layer (similar to 7 mu m in thickness) by a screen printing method.
Titulo: Enhanced electrochemical properties of Bi-layer La0.5Sr0.5CoO3-δ cathode prepared by a hybrid method

Sentencas: By inserting the PLD seed layer with the thickness of similar to 500 nm or less, robust cathode films with desired microstructure and excellent adhesion properties with the underlying electrolyte layer, are successfully fabricated.
Titulo: Enhanced electrochemical properties of Bi-layer La0.5Sr0.5CoO3-δ cathode prepared by a hybrid method

Sentencas: The area specific resistance (ASR) of the hybrid cathode layers decreases about 5 times compared with that of the single layer cathode films prepared by the conventional screen printing method.
Titulo: Enhanced electrochemical properties of Bi-layer La0.5Sr0.5CoO3-δ cathode prepared by a hybrid method

Sentencas: The hybrid approach provides a cost-effective way to fabricate thick cathode films with significantly enhanced electrochemical properties for solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs).
Titulo: Enhanced electrochemical properties of Bi-layer La0.5Sr0.5CoO3-δ cathode prepared by a hybrid method
